.tokensave/

# Cargo build output. Previously ignored only via a personal global gitignore,
# so on any other machine it dirtied the release-input cleanliness check.
target/

# Generated when the workspace test suite builds this test fixture crate.
# Untracked and unignored, it made gascan_assert_release_inputs_clean fail,
# so running the tests made packaging refuse to build a release.
# Scoped deliberately: the workspace Cargo.lock is a tracked release input.
crates/gascan-apple/tests/fixtures/fake-attach-helper/Cargo.lock

# A global gitignore may carry a Visual Studio build-output pattern such as
# [Rr]elease/, which would silently ignore new files in these tracked
# directories. A new release contract test would then fail to commit and never
# run in the gate. Repository rules override the global file, so re-include
# them explicitly.
!docs/release/
!tests/release/
